{
  "stem": "9168.6",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was a chaotic period of time there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I had a one-year contract, which had to have been up sometime around the end of October, '47.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And they wa-- they did not want us to leave.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because that meant they had to recruit other reporters to go over.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "All 13 trials took from November 1945 through beyond-- shortly beyond April of 1949, when the last judgments were rendered in April.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they did not want us to leave.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But at that time, the Berlin Airlift was going on.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And there was a certain amount of anxiety over, are the Russians coming, to the extent that all travel and transportation provided by the US War Department for any of us was canceled.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they were-- they got out all of the Allied personnel wives and children from Berlin because of the Berlin crisis over the Russians.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The Russians were no longer part of the trial process.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But they were still part of the four-power [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] sectioned off areas of Germany.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And of course, they had Berlin.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They had a great, great part of Ber-- Berlin.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I actually made the decision that-- I-- some of us actually told our, our superiors, no, we are not going to start another trial.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because we think if we do, then you are not going to try to get us home.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that-- but that was not a heavy kind of handed-- heavy-handed thing on our part.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We wanted to get home.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I remember, actually, my husband and I going to Brussels and Paris, in particular, to see if I could buy my way on a plane or a ship out of France or Brussels-- a plane, Bremerhaven, Germany, pay my own way.",
      "word_count": 42
    }
  ],
